{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01U4zyAw1jfkEsnDweoSju4J","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No plugins installed. Elasticsearch 7.17.9 needs the `repository-s3` plugin for S3/MinIO snapshots. This is a challenge because:\n1. Installing plugins requires modifying the image or installing at startup\n2. We can't easily install plugins at runtime in a running container without restarting\n\nWait, let me reconsider. Actually `elasticsearch-plugin install` can be run inside a running container and then the node needs to restart. But I need to be careful about this approach.\n\nActually, for Elasticsearch 7.x, the `repository-s3` plugin is needed. I can install it in each pod and then restart the pods. \n\nBut the task says to restart only if needed, and installing the plugin definitely requires a restart. The challenge is that I'd need to install on all three nodes, which requires internet access or a local file, and then trigger rolling restarts. There's a cleaner approach using an init container to handle the plugin installation at startup, but that would require modifying the StatefulSet itself.\n\nLet me think about whether the plugin might already be available offline from the Elasticsearch installation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":421,"cache_read_input_tokens":33792,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":421},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f2053646-cad2-42b8-a6ee-d7faafb0009c","uuid":"8968dae2-392f-4a2a-a624-ec9b7a3b748c","request_id":"req_011Ccew9tpZxTEiCmvKcb49K"}
