{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MzCAbGSMndQgTfsKckf5MU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All components are in place. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Task complete.** Here's what was configured:\n\n1. **`es-secure-settings` Secret created** — stores `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (MinIO credentials `minioadmin`). No credentials in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars.\n\n2. **StatefulSet patched** with two init containers:\n   - `install-plugin`: downloads and installs `repository-s3` plugin on every pod start, copied to a shared emptyDir volume mounted at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/plugins`\n   - `setup-keystore`: creates a fresh keystore, reads credentials from the `es-secure-settings` Secret via env var refs, adds them as keystore entries, and copies to a shared emptyDir mounted at the keystore path\n\n3. **Rolling restart** — all 3 pods cycled through with the new init containers; all 3 nodes now have `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` in their keystores.\n\n4. **MinIO service created** — `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` (the deployment had no Service).\n\n5. **`es-backups` bucket created** in MinIO.\n\n6. **`minio-repo` snapshot repository registered** — S3 type, path-style access, HTTP protocol to MinIO.\n\n7. **`snapshot-1` created successfully** — state `SUCCESS`, 4 shards backed up (0 failures)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":251,"cache_read_input_tokens":80941,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":251},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f2053646-cad2-42b8-a6ee-d7faafb0009c","uuid":"e797a186-01a1-41a2-bec8-14255ef9ae14","request_id":"req_011CceyHkDbkcZrMd